The concentric‑zone model (Burgess) consists of: 
1. CBD (central business district) – commercial core; 
2. Zone 2 – transition zone with mixed uses; 
3. Zone 3 – inner‑city residential (higher density); 
4. Zone 4 – low‑density residential suburbs; 
5. Zone 5 – commuter belt/rural fringe. The diagram labels the outermost ring as "Suburban zone," which corresponds to Zone 4, making option C correct. Options A and B refer to zones closer to the centre with higher density, while D is the CBD itself.
